                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      EC notice to15 parties
          OUR LEGAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, April 24: The Election Commission has slapped showcause notices on 15 political parties, among them the BJP, the RJD and the Janata Dal (Secular), for failing to furnish details of their election expenses in the last Lok Sabha elections.         
	The parties have been asked to reply to the notice by April 29, a release issued by the panel today said. The notices were given on April 16, it said.         
	Action will be taken if the parties do not respond, the commission has said.                                                                                                                                                           
